ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[The evidence for viral infection remains weak, and confirmation must await
the outcome of the second series of tests. The severity and sudden onset of
the illness and the apparent absence of sequelae suggests that a
non-infectious cause cannot be excluded at this stage. One does wonder
whether there is a connection between the earlier reported undiagnosed
outbreak in West Bengal and the above-reported outbreaks in Andrha Pradesh
and Maharastra state; a shared as-yet-unidentified agent either microbial
or toxic? More information from official sources would be welcomed. -
Mods.CP/MPP]
